---
layout: "layouts/default.hbs"
title: "Anthropometry Playground"
---

<article>
  <div class="sticky-settings">
    <div class="grid">
      <details class="nomargin dropdown"
               data-tooltip="Choose the dataset to analyze."
               data-preference-dropdown>
        <summary>Dataset</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="radio" name="dataset" value="ansur1" />
              <span>
                ANSUR I
                <br />
                <small>
                  A survey of U.S. Army personnel published in
                  1988.
                  <br />
                  Includes 140+ measures for 1774 men and 2208
                  women.
                </small>
              </span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <hr />
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="radio" name="dataset" value="ansur2" checked />
              <span>
                ANSUR II
                <small class="badge">(recommended)</small>
                <br />
                <small>
                  A survey of U.S. Army personnel published in
                  2017.
                  <br />
                  Includes 93 measures for 4082 men and 1986
                  women.
                  <br />
                </small>
              </span>
            </label>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details class="nomargin dropdown"
               data-tooltip="Choose the gender(s) to include."
               data-preference-dropdown>
        <summary>Genders</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" name="genderMale" checked />
              Male
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" name="genderFemale" checked />
              Female
            </label>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details class="nomargin dropdown"
               data-tooltip="Choose the units of measurement to use."
               data-preference-dropdown>
        <summary>Units</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="radio" name="unit" value="metric" checked />
              <span>Metric <small>(cm, kg)</small></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <label>
              <input type="radio" name="unit" value="imperial" />
              <span>Imperial <small>(in, lbs)</small></span>
            </label>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </div>
    <hr />
  </div>
  <details name="visualizations1" open>
    <summary class="contrast">001. Actual Distribution</summary>
    <div class="grid visualization-grid">
      <div>
        <p>
          View the distribution of a single anthropometric variable.
          Select the variable to visualize. Enter a value to see where
          it falls within the dataset.
        </p>
        <div>
          <label>X-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementXHistogram" valueName="measurementValueXHistogram" defaultValue="stature" }}
        </div>
      </div>
      {{> components/plots/histogram id="histogram-plot" }}
    </div>
  </details>
  <hr />
  <details name="visualizations2" open>
    <summary class="contrast">002. Actual Joint Distribution</summary>
    <div class="grid visualization-grid">
      <div>
        <p>
          View the joint distribution between two anthropometric
          variables. Select the variables to visualize. Enter a value
          for each to see where that point falls within the dataset.
        </p>
        <div>
          <label>X-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementXScatter" valueName="measurementValueXScatter" defaultValue="stature" }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <label>Y-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementYScatter" valueName="measurementValueYScatter" defaultValue="weight" }}
        </div>
      </div>
      {{> components/plots/scatter id="scatter-plot" }}
    </div>
  </details>
  <hr />
  <details name="visualizations3" open>
    <summary class="contrast">003. Modelled Probability Distribution</summary>
    <div class="grid visualization-grid">
      <div>
        <p>
          View the modelled probability distribution for a single anthropometric variable.
          Select the variable to visualize. Enter a value to see where
          it falls within the dataset.
        </p>
        <div>
          <label>X-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementXDensity" valueName="measurementValueXDensity" defaultValue="stature" }}
        </div>
        <div>
          {{> components/controls/switch id="densitySigmaToggle" name="densitySigmaToggle" label="Show Sigma Lines" checked=false }}
        </div>
      </div>
      {{> components/plots/density id="density-plot" }}
    </div>
  </details>
  <hr />
  <details name="visualizations4" open>
    <summary class="contrast">004. Modelled Joint Probability Distribution</summary>
    <div class="grid visualization-grid">
      <div>
        <p>
          View the modelled joint probability density for two anthropometric variables.
          Select the variables to visualize. Enter a value for each to see where that point falls within the dataset.
        </p>
        <div>
          <label>X-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementXJointDensity" valueName="measurementValueXJointDensity" defaultValue="stature" }}
        </div>
        <div>
          <label>Y-Axis:</label>
          {{> components/controls/measurement name="measurementYJointDensity" valueName="measurementValueYJointDensity" defaultValue="weight" }}
        </div>
        <div>
          {{> components/controls/switch id="jointDensitySigmaToggle" name="jointDensitySigmaToggle" label="Show Sigma Lines" checked=false }}
        </div>
      </div>
      {{> components/plots/joint-density id="joint-density-plot" }}
    </div>
  </details>
</article>
